HEADWORD: Water mint
<hw>Wa"ter mint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A kind of mint (<spn>Mentha
aquatica</spn>) growing in wet places, and sometimes having a perfume
resembling bergamot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

